HEADWORD: Cephalaspis
<hw>Ceph`a*las"pis</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr.
Gr. <grk>kefalh`</grk> head + <?/ a shield.]</ety> <fld>(Paleon.)</fld>
<def>A genus of fossil ganoid fishes found in the old red sandstone or
Devonian formation. The head is large, and protected by a broad
shield-shaped helmet prolonged behind into two lateral points.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

